### getQualifiedNameIndex() {#aa755805a8a835eba37c76377d871d3b0}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static std::optional&lt; uint32&#95;t &gt; getQualifiedNameIndex (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfdie">DWARFDie</a> &amp; Die, uint64&#95;t Language, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/gsym/gsymcreator">GsymCreator</a> &amp; Gsym)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Get the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/gsym/gsymcreator">GsymCreator</a> string table offset for the qualified name for the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> passed in.

This function will avoid making copies of any strings in the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/gsym/gsymcreator">GsymCreator</a> when possible. We don&#39;t need to copy a string when the string comes from our .debug&#95;str section or is an inlined string in the .debug&#95;info. If we create a qualified name string in this function by combining multiple strings in the DWARF string table or info, we will make a copy of the string when we add it to the string table.

Definition at line <a href="#l00132">132</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/gsym/dwarftransformer-cpp">DwarfTransformer.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
